1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:07,625
A live event is a team sport.

2
00:00:07,925 --> 00:00:10,175
Director, stage managers, AV engineers, interpreters,

3
00:00:10,475 --> 00:00:13,475
registration desk — everyone needs the right information,

4
00:00:13,775 --> 00:00:15,775
and only the right information.

5
00:00:16,075 --> 00:00:18,700
CueDeck handles this with six distinct roles,

6
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:21,250
each with a tailored view and

7
00:00:21,550 --> 00:00:23,550
a specific set of permissions.

8
00:00:23,850 --> 00:00:25,850
The Director sees everything.

9
00:00:26,150 --> 00:00:28,400
Full session list, full context panel,

10
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:30,950
all action buttons — Set Ready,

11
00:00:31,250 --> 00:00:34,625
Go Live, Hold, End, nudge, delay cascade, signage, broadcast.

12
00:00:34,925 --> 00:00:37,550
This is the person running the show.

13
00:00:37,850 --> 00:00:41,600
Stage Managers get the session list with status badges and

14
00:00:41,900 --> 00:00:44,150
the ability to mark speaker arrivals.

15
00:00:44,450 --> 00:00:47,075
They can transition sessions — Set Ready,

16
00:00:47,375 --> 00:00:49,375
Call Speaker, Go Live.

17
00:00:49,675 --> 00:00:51,925
They don't see financials or settings.

18
00:00:52,225 --> 00:00:54,850
AV engineers see what's LIVE right now,

19
00:00:55,150 --> 00:00:58,900
what's coming next, and the recording/streaming flags on each session.

20
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:01,825
They don't need the full programme —

21
00:01:02,125 --> 00:01:04,375
just what's relevant to their setup.

22
00:01:04,675 --> 00:01:07,675
Interpretation booths get a clean queue view —

23
00:01:07,975 --> 00:01:10,225
current session, next session, language flags.

24
00:01:10,525 --> 00:01:13,900
If a session has interpretation enabled, it shows here.

25
00:01:14,200 --> 00:01:16,200
No clutter.

26
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:18,750
Registration desk sees who's on stage,

27
00:01:19,050 --> 00:01:21,675
what's next, and can check in arrivals.

28
00:01:21,975 --> 00:01:23,975
Simple, focused.

29
00:01:24,275 --> 00:01:27,275
Signage operators manage the digital display panel —

30
00:01:27,575 --> 00:01:30,950
adding and configuring screens, changing modes, uploading sponsor logos.

31
00:01:31,250 --> 00:01:33,500
They don't touch sessions at all.

32
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:36,050
To add someone to your event,

33
00:01:36,350 --> 00:01:38,350
go to the team panel.

34
00:01:38,650 --> 00:01:40,650
Click Invite Operator.

35
00:01:40,950 --> 00:01:42,950
Enter their email address.

36
00:01:43,250 --> 00:01:45,250
Choose their role.

37
00:01:45,550 --> 00:01:47,550
Hit Send Invite.

38
00:01:47,850 --> 00:01:50,850
They get an email with a magic link.

39
00:01:51,150 --> 00:01:54,525
They click it, set their password if they're new,

40
00:01:54,825 --> 00:01:58,575
and they're in — automatically scoped to your event with

41
00:01:58,875 --> 00:02:00,875
the role you assigned.

42
00:02:01,175 --> 00:02:04,925
The invite is tied to you as the event director.

43
00:02:05,225 --> 00:02:08,975
If they're already a CueDeck user they just get access

44
00:02:09,275 --> 00:02:11,275
to your event instantly.

45
00:02:11,575 --> 00:02:14,200
Not sure what a role can do?

46
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:18,250
Hit the question mark in the header, then Quick Reference.

47
00:02:18,550 --> 00:02:22,300
You'll see a full table of every state transition and

48
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:24,600
which roles can trigger it.

49
00:02:24,900 --> 00:02:26,900
Directors get everything.

50
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:29,200
Stage managers get transitions.

51
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:32,125
AV and Interp are read-only for sessions.

52
00:02:32,425 --> 00:02:35,050
This is your field reference during production.

53
00:02:35,350 --> 00:02:37,350
Six roles, zero confusion.

54
00:02:37,650 --> 00:02:40,650
Everyone sees what they need, nothing they don't.

55
00:02:40,950 --> 00:02:44,700
In the next episode we'll look at the broadcast bar

56
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:49,875
— how you send real-time messages to every connected device on your team.

57
00:02:50,175 --> 00:02:53,175
Subscribe and I'll see you in episode five.
